## Upload #1 — `wp04-smoke-test.md` (Symfony detected as text/plain)

```
POST http://127.0.0.1:8080/sagamok-anishnawbek/manage/ingestion
Content-Type: multipart/form-data
=> 422 Unprocessable Entity
   Body: "No handler supports MIME type: text/plain"
```

**Interpretation**: Request passed `CsrfMiddleware`. Reached `IngestionHandlerRegistry`. Registry returned 422 because no handler is registered for `text/plain` (giiken's registered handlers are `text/csv`, `text/html`, `text/markdown`, Word/PDF). The `.md` file's MIME was inferred as `text/plain` by Symfony's MIME detector for this small ASCII payload.

