## Browser cookie state (captured via Playwright `browser_evaluate`)

```
document.cookie = "PHPSESSID=b61dc2dfa9bd2d274158ff3226e994e6; XSRF-TOKEN=ab9699fee87c274ceb33c01d5e4bc68131eeab21102567fe817b852b19b3c3ad"
```

- **`XSRF-TOKEN` cookie present** → satisfies FR-001.
- **JS-readable** → cookie has no `HttpOnly` flag (otherwise `document.cookie` could not see it) → satisfies the contract §1 cookie-attribute requirement.
- **Token value** is 64 hex chars, matching `bin2hex(random_bytes(32))` from `CsrfMiddleware::token()`.
- **Inertia/axios behavior**: The Inertia-bundled axios client auto-forwards `XSRF-TOKEN` as `X-XSRF-TOKEN` on same-origin state-changing requests. This is built into axios; no giiken JavaScript was modified to make it work. That is the "zero consumer-side wiring" outcome promised by FR-008.

