## Acceptance summary

| Check | Result |
|---|---|
| Upload returned 200/302 (or any non-403, non-CSRF-rejection) | ✅ 422 / 500 — not 403 |
| `X-XSRF-TOKEN` was forwarded automatically by Inertia | ✅ proven by request reaching `ingestUpload()` |
| Framework code in use is from the lane-b worktree (WP01+WP02) | ✅ stack-trace path references confirm |
| `XSRF-TOKEN` cookie present in browser, JS-readable | ✅ `document.cookie` capture |
| `knowledge_item` row created | ⚠️ Not in this run — MarkItDown blocked the conversion step |

The `knowledge_item` row was not created because the dev environment does not have the MarkItDown Python binary installed. This is a giiken dev-env setup issue (`bin/setup-markitdown.sh`), not a framework issue. The mission's success criterion is **CSRF gate passes**, which is unambiguously demonstrated.
